 align=left class=m><span class=title>   New recruiting suggestions</span><hr size=1> Well, today the board is working so I'll post what I meant to yesterday.As many of you know, I am now head of recruiting, and I feel it is needed to post some sort of guideline that officers and myself can use.So,here goes nothing.<br>
1.New recruits to Benevolent Order that are friends of current guildmembers can get in if they are at least of level 15.<br>
2.New recruits who are NOT friends of current members shall be level 20 or higher.<br>
<br>
and most IMPORTANTLY <br>
3. If you have any questions/objections/opionions/suggestions PLEASE either send me a tell in game or send me an e-mail, though I am head recruiter, I am here to represent all of you, and feedback is the only was I can get a feel for how I am doing.<br>
and last but certainly not least for those involved.<br>
4. If I am the recruiting officer that performs the invite, upon invite you shall recieve the following: Skin Like Nature, Strength Of Storms,Chloroplast, Spirit of Wolf, and Shield of Thorns as part of my welcoming &quot;gift basket&quot;.<br>
<br>
You can reach me at cdc608@aol.com or in game on Tienen .<br>
<br>
Hope to hear from you all,<br>
<br>
Tienen Crazywolf &lt;Benevolent Order&gt;<br>
Druid follower of Tunare of the 50th Level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valmar>Valmar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/11/00 2:22:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sounds great to me!</span><hr size=1> Hey Tienen,<br>
     Sounds like a great plan to me and hopefully will work well.<br>
<br>
Valmar Ranthorn Noble Knight of Truth of Mithaniel Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ufaadno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faadno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/11/00 4:55:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/sd/chaosfactor/faadno.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New recruiting suggestions</span><hr size=1> I think that the restriction should be changed to a lower level for all.  I think once a person hits 10 they should be able to join our guild.  I know many will disagree but this is how I see it.  When Em first started this guild guess what level she was?  She was level 16 I believe.  She then invited Kiglan who was level 12 and myself who was level 8 at the time.  This was in Early January of 2000. Now just because most of the guild is high level doesn't mean that there cannot be a lower level bunch in the guild.  This is an issue I have been thinking of while I have been afk for 5 months. (DOH!)  I have been on about 10 times in that span of 5 months <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and I have joined another mid level guild called Black Magic.  I did that because I would always have someone to group with when I logged on the very few times.  I have been wanting to join the benevolent order again since I quit in april when school ended.  After reading some of the rules and the little civil war so to speak on people quitting and such.  I haven't decided if I should join.  The Ben Order has become a guild of high level people who snub the lower levels.  Big deal they don't play as much EQ as the rest of you.  Doesn't mean they should automatically be put in the can't join area.  This is one of my pet peves in this game where people limit their guild recruiting to a high level/all I do is play EQ rule.  Just remember that EM, Kig and myself were in this guild way before anyone ever hit level 20 and it worked out fine.  Just have the lowbies plan their own raids etc.  If you want to pull yourselves away from your 50hours straight of burning out on EQ and help the lowbies out then go ahead.  I feel that if the limit is set to 20 the guild will stop growing and people will start to quit out of pure boredom.  I have nothing against any of you but this rule sucks.  I have been playing EQ since december of 1999 and have only logged in total between 3 chars being Faadno (my primary) Senladar (my old level 14 sk) and Senladaer my current secondary level 9 warrior for about 20 days of playing.  Faadno has 14 days and the other 6 were done on other chars.  Now check your /played and see how much time you have spent on playing a sur-real persona and then add all of your chars up.  That is what I am talking about.  Keeping newbies/lowbies out of the guild goes against most of what the guild (I thought) stood for which was to help people enjoy this game more.  I remember when I was about to quit playing at level 8 and then emanie came by and helped me cross from Qeynos to Freeport.  This kept my interest up in the game and I am still playing it.  So if helping others out is not the way of the Benevolent Order then maybe the name should be changed to the (Only High level/EQ burnouts order.<br>
<br>
Sorry I got so personal but I am tired of level caps and bias towards new players who want to have a good time and need some help. &quot;Benevolent&quot;<br>
<br>
Faadno out. <p><APPLET codebase="http://www.angelfire.com/sd/chaosfactor/" CODE="fadein.class"
