</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=idella>Idella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/17/00 10:57:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New recruiting suggestions</span><hr size=1> I am in complete agreeance with Faadno on this one. I just started playing again after my extended hiatus as Kavin and the guild has changed almost completely. The real fun of the guild was the fact that we were ALL low levels, we need eachother. We were forced to group just to accomplish even the simple tasks and that was the great part about it. I remember the beginnings too. Heck, I was one of the first members when Emanie and ole Stump came by to induct me into a wonderful, social guild. I do not know what has happened in the past few months but I can see that instead of the usual ten members on at a time, we have dwindled to more like four. I do not think the restrictions should be set so high. What is wrong with low levels anyway? I think ten is a perfectly acceptable number. Just enough time to know who that person is and what they have done for Norrath. So, on a final note, I would just like to remind people that we are the Benevolent Order and should hold true to our name. Be kind and generous, not vindictive or self-righteous.<br>
<br>
::gets off soap box::<br>
<br>
Thank you.<br>
<br>
Idella, lvl 13 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valmar>Valmar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/00 1:24:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Doh!</span><hr size=1> Well it seems I must redeem myself, seems when we had the vote I was all for the 10 lvl limit too but alas I guess more ppl voted for higher lvls. But in fact I do agree with the lvl 10 limit for you see when I first started adventuring I felt like when I was lvl 10 that I had enough of a grasp of EQ to be able to hold my own, I wish others would feel that way also especially now that our numbers have dwindled we need the new blood more than ever to hold what we have. I am not going anywhere though, this is my third guild and it will be my final rest assured. As I have told a couple of ppl before my first guild was Knights of the Realm and it went down hard and I don't want to see this happen to ours. I hope everyone still here is willing to weather the storm because I think we have a great guild and it can rise again like the phoenix and please if anyone needs help or needs anything within reason of course please let me know I am more than willing to help, that is my two cps or less so now I will get off my soap box, thanks Idella and Faadno for waking me up and giving a fresh perspective to what I have been feeling all along.<br>
<br>
Valmar Ranthorn a rather confused Knight of Truth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/00 5:42:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~stinnett/Girasmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Doh!</span><hr size=1> Now that our guild is primarily made up of people in the 10-15 and 27-32 ranges, I agree that we may want to recruit some younger folks.  Since more than half of the guild has left, we are left in need of some members to fill gaps.  Hopefully we can figure something out soon.  Sure wish Emanie and Elupis would show up sometime!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><font face="verdana,arial" size="1">-Giradella Broomrider (Benevolent Order)<br>
